Here are ten invaluable writing tips from the master himself, @MatthewDicks. Scroll for storytelling ğŸ“–
@MatthewDicks 1. Homework for life

My favourite tip from Matthew; pick one moment from every day to write down, and soon youâ€™ll begin to find trends and stories you can write about. I love doing this and looking back at the end of each month to see what I picked out.
@MatthewDicks 2. Clarity is your goal

The best stories arenâ€™t the most elaborate, inventive, or spectacular. They are small moments - told with absolute clarity.
@MatthewDicks 3. No stand up comedy

Thereâ€™s no harm in making people laugh when you tell a story, but itâ€™s important to remember that story-telling is not as funny as stand up. They are different skills and translate differently on the page.
@MatthewDicks 4. Change is relatable

Stories are compelling because they show change over time. We love reflection, transformation, character growth. Without these things, you have an anecdote, not a story.
@MatthewDicks 5. The harsh truth about vacation stories

No one wants to hear about your vacation ğŸ™ƒ
@MatthewDicks 6. Even if youâ€™re struggling, write it down

Staring at a blank page can be really intimidating. When I have an idea, I start writing without putting pressure on myself. Getting words down on a page begin to give your idea structure and makes it feel more manageable.
@MatthewDicks 8. Five magical seconds

Matthew says â€œDonâ€™t get hung up on the big moments, the unbelievable circumstances, or the hilarious details. Seek out the moments when you felt your heart moveâ€¦

Until you have it, you donâ€™t have a story.â€
@MatthewDicks 9. Bridge the gap

Storytelling is all about connecting with your audience. Excitement isnâ€™t actually very important - instead, we want to create a space of vulnerability and honesty with another person.
@MatthewDicks 10. End with heart

Donâ€™t finish your story on a cheap laugh. End with something authentic, moving or thought-provoking. This is what we read / listen to stories for, and it will make yours more memorable.
